{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Line a springform pan with parchment paper and set aside.","Place crackers into mixing bowl and crush <nobr>7 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>.","Add butter and mix <nobr>25 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Spread mixture in base of springform pan. Press crumb mixture firmly using a spoon or your hands to make an even and firm base. Place in refrigerator to chill while making cheese topping. Clean mixing bowl.","Place milk into mixing bowl and warm <nobr>3 min\/160°F\/speed 3<\/nobr>.","Add gelatin by sprinkling into mixing bowl while avoiding blades and edges and mix <nobr>30 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Add olives, (reserving an additional 15 or 16 for decoration), ricotta , Gorgonzola, salt and pepper and mix <nobr>30 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Pour mixture over base and spread out evenly.","Cover with cling wrap and allow to cool in refrigerator for at least 4 hours. Garnish with additional olives halfway through cooling time, or immediately before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["4 ½ oz salted crackers","3 oz unsalted butter, softened, cut into small pieces","7 oz whole milk","4 ½ tsp unflavored gelatin powder","2 oz green olives, pitted, plus 15-16 extra, to garnish","9 oz ricotta cheese, well drained","7 oz Gorgonzola, creamy, or other blue cheese","1 pinch salt","1 pinch freshly ground pepper"]}],"id":"r119808","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-ny2nXe4Oif0\/XZMt1n-WfsI\/AAAAAAAAZ-A\/YgblMUOJ-sIBHnkvQeSIPAueiLkB6o2EACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_1xQZszKaJAtUOt5U.png","title":"Italian Savory Cheesecake","publishedAt":"2017-03-17T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"8 g","fat":"16 g","uom":"per 1 slice","carbohydrates":"9 g","calories":"902 kJ \/ 216 kcal"},"usefulItems":"springform pan (10 in.), parchment paper, cling wrap, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["Ricotta cheese can be replaced with quark, Cloumage Cheese®, Fromage Frais, mascarpone, sour cream or crème fraiche.","Italian Savory Cheescake compliments a charcuterie platter.","Serve smaller slices as a starter with proscuitto or with bread, fruit, crackers and wine at a party.","Pitted olives can be replaced with <nobr>3 oz<\/nobr> walnuts.","Gelatin powder can be replaced with 8 gelatin sheets: follow package instructions to hydrate gelatin and add in step 6."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","4h 20m","12 slices"]}